Beginning Wednesday, September 9th, USD #452 will be providing a free breakfast and a free lunch, Monday through Friday to any child ages 1-18. Any non school aged child who wishes to participate needs to sign up in advance. You may contact Sara Cox at sara.cox@usd452.org to sign up. Meals must be picked up at The junior/senior high school or the elementary school. Breakfast is served from 7:45-8:05 am, grab and go breakfast is served from 9:00-9:50 am and lunch is served from 11:00 am to 1:30 pm.

post_text:
Stanton County High School graduation will be held July 11th at 10:00
am at the high school football stadium. Spectator seating will be on
the football field and we will have painted areas for families to sit
together. Please don’t sit in the walkways! Additional overflow
seating is available outside of the football field end zones and in
the visitors’ stands. We ask that you if you are seated with
non-family members that you maintain six feet of distance, even if
seated within a painted square.

Plan to bring lawn chairs or a blanket to sit on. No chairs will be
provided. Handicapped seating on the track or near the parking area
will be available.

We encourage you to bring your own mask to wear.

post_text:
School Meals information!

As of March 23, 2020, we will be offering Grab & Go breakfast and lunch available to all children ages 1-18 years old. We will have three pickup locations including; Stanton County High School in the parking lot, Big Bow school at the corner of Big Bow Grade and Fourth Ave, and at Manter school in the south parking lot. If you have children that live in rural Stanton County and are unable to get to one of the drop off locations let us know and we will run bus routes and drop these meals off for them.

If you would like for your child/children to have these meals please email or text at opaa@usd452.org. Leave your last name, how many meals for children, and at which site they will pick up or if they are on the bus route.

Please if there are any changes let us know so we aren’t preparing and sending extra meals. We will happily have one available for them. Serving times will be 11:30 am – 1:00 pm, Monday through Friday on regularly scheduled school days.

Stanton County USD 452
March 17 at 9:46 PM ·

Kansas Governor has mandated all schools in Kansas be closed to normal activities until the end of May. This doesn’t mean there is no school. All students will be out of school next week. Faculty and staff of USD 452 will meet next week to develop a continual learning plan to be implemented for the remainder of the school year. Guidance in the development of the continual learning plan is being provided by KSDE. The plan can include online learning, paper packets sent home, small group learning at the school or any other strategy developed by the faculty and staff that is approved by KSDE as part of the continual learning plan. Look for information tonight or tomorrow from the superintendent’s office.

post_text:
Dear Parents/Guardians,

This Wednesday, March 4, our 7-12th grade students will be traveling to Lakin for a presentation. The presenter will be former NBA player, Chris Herren. Mr. Herren will be speaking about the dangers of substance abuse, and he will be sharing from his life experiences.

The students and staff will be leaving at 8:30 a.m. and will be returning to the school at around 1:00 p.m. This will be considered a normal day of school, so if they are not going to attend, they need to be excused by a parent. Sack lunches will be taken, or students have been given the option to bring their own lunch.

If you have any questions, please contact Mr. Siebert at the HS office 620-492-6284.

Thank you!

Great FFA Week activity-Town Tag. (Thanks to Kiowa County FFA for the idea.)These are the only pictures I have from Town Tag tonight-advisor fail!!! We had about 60 kids that worked in teams to make it from the high school to the Battin Park sign and back without getting tagged! The kids were excited all week and want to do it again. Thanks to our taggers Jeff and Azuree Jones, Jim Sipes, Liz Harms, Trenton Horn, Trevor and Rachelle Siebert, and Donnie Morgan. We had several others in town that volunteered to “tag” and that was greatly appreciated. (We will contact you again.) This will be marked down as a win!
